  "content": " .into_iter()\n            .map(|(r, _score)| r)\n            .filter(|r| visibility_filter(r, &opts.visibility, opts.agent_id.as_deref()))\n            .take(opts.limit)\n            .collect();\n\n        let post_filter_count = filtered.len();\n\n        info!(\n            vector_count,\n            graph_expanded,\n            post_filter_count,\n            latency_ms = start.elapsed().as_millis() as u64,\n            \"rag_retrieved\"\n        );\n\n        Ok(RetrievalResult {\n            results: filtered,\n            metrics: RetrievalMetrics {\n                latency_ms: start.elapsed().as_millis() as u64,\n                vector_results: vector_count,\n                graph_expanded,\n                post_filter_count,\n                retriever_name: self.name().into(),\n            },\n        })\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Step 4: Run tests to verify they pass**\n\nRun: `cargo test -p corvia-kernel -- retriever::tests --nocapture`\nExpected: all 5 tests PASS\n\n**Step 5: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add crates/corvia-kernel/src/retriever.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(m3.2): GraphExpandRetriever — vector + graph edge expansion with α blending\"\n```\n\n---\n",
